{"id":24742,"date":"2025-07-11T04:30:33","date_gmt":"2025-07-11T11:30:33","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/?p=24742"},"modified":"2025-07-11T04:30:33","modified_gmt":"2025-07-11T11:30:33","slug":"china-guangxi-west-hainan","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2025\/07\/11\/china-guangxi-west-hainan\/","title":{"rendered":"CHINA &#8211; GUANGXI WEST, HAINAN"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><strong><br \/>\nGUANGXI WEST (Nanning, Baise, Hechi, Qinzhou) transit<\/p>\n<p>NANNING<br \/>\n<\/strong>History, Culture, National and City Museums<br \/>\nNanning: Guangxi Museum of Nationalities<br \/>\nNanning: Guangxi Provincial Museum<br \/>\nNanning: Nanning Museum<br \/>\nNatural History and Earth Museums: Nanning: Geological Museum of Guangxi<br \/>\nScience, Technology and all Industry and Mining Museums: Nanning: Science and Technology Museum<br \/>\nBotanical Gardens: Guangxi Medicinal Botanical Garden<\/p>\n<p><strong>ZUOJIANG HUASHAN ROCK ART CULTURAL LANDSCAPE WHS <\/strong>comprises thousands of pictographs, painted on steep cliff faces along the river in a karst landscape.<br \/>\nThe paintings were made between the 5th century BCE to the 2nd century CE by the Luoyue people. The site is a cultural landscape and also includes hamlets and villages where people still perform rituals connected to the rock art. They cover four distinct phases of painting and include depictions of bronze drums, ferry boats and human figures.<br \/>\nThe pictographs, spread across three locations, can be seen from boats that navigate the river and wooden platforms on the opposite bank.<br \/>\n<strong>Get There:<\/strong> 2h bus from Nanning Jiangnan Station<br \/>\n<strong>Zhoulian dock.<\/strong> The first boat leaves at 11.30. large and covered, like a small cruise ship. A guide, almost an hour on the light sandstone walls. Ningming Huashan is the largest panel containing 1951 of a total of 4050 paintings. Are so many drawings on that one cliff that from a distance it almost looks red. There is little variation with the vast majority of them portray people (dancing puppets), there are circles with a star (representing bronze drums) and dogs. All this is linked to the ritual activities of the surrounding villages. There are no drawings of daily activities, as is common elsewhere in rock art.<br \/>\nNanning has rock art copies to decorate lamp posts, supermarket roofs, even the factory chimneys. Many of the rocks walls are covered with scaffolding. Spend more time stopping at the local village for the inevitable shopping,<br \/>\nMost people find the art disappointing.<\/p>\n<p>Islands<strong>: <\/strong>Weizhou Island<br \/>\nAirports: Beihai (BHY), Nanning (NNG)<br \/>\n<strong>Waterfalls: <\/strong>Ban Gioc \u2013 Detian Falls<strong><br \/>\nBeaches: <\/strong>Beihei: Silver Beach<br \/>\n<strong>XINGPING<\/strong> village<br \/>\n<strong>DARE<\/strong><br \/>\nWeizhou island<br \/>\nXilin country (westernmost)<br \/>\n<strong>++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++<\/strong><\/p>\n<p><strong>GUANGXI EAST (Guilin, Liuzhou, Yulin, Guigang, Laibin) good visit <\/strong><br \/>\n<strong>Airports: <\/strong>Guilin (KWL)<strong>, <\/strong>Liuzhou (LZH)<br \/>\n<strong>History, Culture, National and City Museums<br \/>\n<\/strong>Guangxi: Guilin Museum<strong><br \/>\n<\/strong>Guangxi: Jingjiang King Mausoleum Museum<br \/>\n<strong>Religious Temples<br \/>\n<\/strong>Guiping: Xishi Temple<strong><br \/>\nWorld of Nature: <\/strong>Longsheng Longji Terraced Field National Wetland Park<br \/>\n<strong>Caves, Sinkholes and Saltmines<br \/>\n<\/strong>Guilin: Reed Flute Cave<strong><br \/>\n<\/strong>Seven-Star Cave<br \/>\n<strong>++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++<\/strong><\/p>\n<p><strong>HAINAN<\/strong><\/p>\n<p><strong>HAIKOU<br \/>\nHistory, Culture, National and City Museums: <\/strong>Haikou: Provincial Museum<strong><br \/>\nBotanical Gardens: <\/strong>Haikou: Hainan Tropical Wildlife Park and Botanical Garden<strong><br \/>\nLighthouses: <\/strong>Haikou: Baishamen Lighthouse<\/p>\n<p>DARE:<br \/>\n<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Disputed (China\/Vietnam) &#8211; Paracel<\/span><br \/>\nDisputed (China\/Vietnam\/Malaysia\/Brunei\/Taiwan\/Philippines) \u2013 Spratly islands<\/p>\n<p><strong>Tentative WHS<br \/>\n<\/strong>Dongzhai Port Nature Reserve (12\/02\/1996)<strong><br \/>\n<\/strong>Hainan Tropical Rainforest and the Traditional Settlement of Li Ethnic Group<br \/>\nTushuihe Miao Ethnic Village. VILLAGE<br \/>\n<strong>Lighthouses:<br \/>\n<\/strong>Qionghai: Bo&#8217;ao Lighthouse<strong><br \/>\n<\/strong>Wenchang: Mulantou Lighthouse<\/p>\n<p><strong>SANYA<br \/>\n<\/strong>Airports: Haikou (HAK), Sanya (SYX)<br \/>\n<strong>Architectural Delights: <\/strong><a href=\"https:\/\/maps.google.com\/?cid=17438808250110132022\">Sanya: Sanya Beauty Crown Hotel<\/a><strong><br \/>\nReligious Temples: <\/strong>Sanya: Nanshan Temple<strong><br \/>\nReligious Monuments: <\/strong>Sanya: Guanyin of Nanshan<strong><br \/>\nBeaches<br \/>\n<\/strong>Sanya: Wuzhizhou Island<strong><br \/>\n<\/strong>Sanya: Yalong Bay<br \/>\n<strong>World of Nature<br \/>\n<\/strong>Bawangling National Nature Reserve<strong><br \/>\n<\/strong>Hainan Tropical Rainforest NP<strong><br \/>\n<\/strong>Wuzhishan National Nature Reserve<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>GUANGXI WEST (Nanning, Baise, Hechi, Qinzhou) transit NANNING History, Culture, National and City Museums Nanning: Guangxi Museum of Nationalities Nanning: Guangxi Provincial Museum Nanning: Nanning Museum Natural History and Earth Museums: Nanning: Geological Museum of Guangxi Science, Technology and all &hellip; <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2025\/07\/11\/china-guangxi-west-hainan\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"c